original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses ANSI escape codes, specifically the sequence `\033[32m` to set the color to green. You can combine this with the desired text and then reset the color back to default with `\033[0m`. For instance:

```
\033[32mGreen Text\033[0m
```

This will display "Green Text" in green color in a compatible terminal emulator that recognizes ANSI escape codes.
